<Author>Pippero
<Content>Not very good value for your $$$ We stayed there one night, hence we did not need to use the kitchen. The sleeping area had looked new or renovated; the two queen beds were very comfortable. The kitchen was a different game, because apart of the refrigerator and microwave, that looked new, the rest of the furniture looked cheap and aged, as well as the bathroom, that shown its age. The tap of the tub was broken 鈥?we could not cut the water; we called the front desk and the tap was immediately repaired. Other problem with the TV set; the volume could not go down to a night level, so at an hour we shut it down not to annoy the neighbour rooms. The wi-fi was available only at a fee (5$) when the motel near offered it for free, as many other around. Considering that we paid 71$ plus taxes, we believe it is overpriced for what it offers. 
