<Author>R.Blair
<Content>Low expectations not even met! I wasn't expecting much and was still disappointed. If you don't need a kitchen, don't bother. The outside looks nice, but the inside is old and has horrible mattresses!!! There was no bedding for the pull out bed. Not just in the room, in the whole hotel. It's supposed to come equiped. Well, we had four of us. It was supposed to have a setting for three. Missing silverware. It had some dishes, but plan to bring your own soap to wash the dishes. The plug in the hotel broke my daughters waterpik for her teeth. The toaster would burn one side of the toast and not even cook the other side. I had to pay a larger rate ($75.00/night) because of Spring Break. It wasn't worth it. I am pretty liberal with hotels, especially when I KNOW it's not the nicest. But really, I wouldn't stay here unless you reaaaallllly have to. 
