<Author>Abal
<Content>Find another place to stay. This motel says it caters to exended stays... but the minute we walked in we disliked it. I had expected 'basic accomadations', but this was just unpleasant and uncomfortable.  The room was run down and threadbare, with rips in the sofa, and marks on the walls and cabinets. It was not clean -- sticky surfaces on the counter tops. The coffeemaker was dirty and stained. We had reserved a 2 bed room, which they did not have. Gave us one bed and a single pull out bed, both of which were lumpy (so were the pillows). There was no bedding for the pullout, so we had to go to the office to get it. Only one person was working on the property, so he did not come to the room with the bedding. The pullout was right next to the air conditioner/heater which blew air all night. The windows were cracked above the locks, fortunately ours was a 2nd floor end unit so the window was not reachable from the outside, as most are. The towels were stiff and thin. There was no shampoo. This is the only motel I have ever stayed in where they expect you to empty your own trash. The price, though lower than many in town at the time, was still significantly overpriced considering the poor condition of the room and beds. 
