<Author>Dee_Elaine
<Content>Very Helpful Staff We returned home three days ago from a week-long stay at Studio 6, Deer Valley in Phoenix. It's a great value and nicer than we expected! Bed was better than adequate. They said even the bedspread is washed after each guest leaves. Everything was clean and like new, except some problems with the refrigerator. It stayed cold OK, but leaked once a day and they couldn't seem to fix it permanently. Don't stay in Room 226 unless it is fixed.We like our privacy, so we thought it was a plus to not have daily maid service. As many towels as you want are available at the front desk. A movie theatre is less than a mile away, and several chain grocery stores are close. Freeway 17 is 1/2 block away.The nicest thing about staying there was the friendly helpful staff. They were all nice. For an inexpensive place, we'd give it a 90. 
