<Author>Grettasmith
<Content>Good Value for the Money We stayed at this facility 9 nights during the Barrett-Jackson car auction. It is located appx 17 miles north of there. The room was a King with a couch and all the other ammentites as listed. My only issues was the carpet needed to be shampooed and the corners near the couch and around the bed were not vacumed sufficiently. Also I had to wait appx 4 hours on day #2 for clean linen as I noticed stains on the thermal blanket so I stripped the ENTIRE bed! However, I was given new mattress pads and a thermal blanket which was a good as I would want it! The pots were cheap and bendable but pratical. We paid $38 night for 2 adults so it was worth the money, most other people paid over $200 night to attend the auction. I would certainly stay again, the visit was average,not bad,not excellent, just average. One front desk staff attendent did tell me how tired she was which I thought was very unprofessional. As a bonus fresh Otis Spunkmeyer cookies are baked each night for guest:) 
